<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="<%= settings.colorScheme %>">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Admin Panel - ProductForge CTF Challenge</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
  <script src="/js/script.js" defer></script>
</head>
<body class="font-size-<%= settings.fontSize %>">
  <header>
    <div class="logo">
      <h1>Product<span>Forge</span></h1>
    </div>
    <nav>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="/products">Products</a></li>
        <li><a href="/customize">Customize</a></li>
        <!-- <li><a href="/hints">Hints</a></li> -->
        <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
        <li><a href="/check-admin" class="admin-link">Admin</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="layout-flexbox">
    <% if (typeof feedback !== 'undefined' && feedback) { %>
      <div class="feedback-message">
        <%= feedback %>
      </div>
    <% } %>
    <div class="layout-<%= settings.layout %>"></div>
    <section class="admin-section">
      <h2>Admin Panel</h2>
      
      <div class="congrats-message">
        <h3>Congratulations!</h3>
        <p>You've successfully exploited the prototype pollution vulnerability.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flag-container">
        <h3>Here's your flag:</h3>
        <div class="flag">
          <code><%= flag %></code>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="explanation">
        <h3>How it worked:</h3>
        <p>The vulnerable <code>mergeObjects</code> function allowed you to pollute the Object prototype.</p>
        <p>By adding the <code>isAdmin</code> property to the Object prototype, every object in the application inherited this property.</p>
        <p>This is a classic example of prototype pollution, a vulnerability that occurs when an attacker is able to add or modify properties of JavaScript's Object prototype.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2025 ProductForge CTF Challenge</p>
    <p class="subtle-hint">Created By Debmalya Saha</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>